{"questionId":"9066602","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Aspirin can be obtained from salicylic acid.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Additional information can be obtained from the <sup>1</sup>H NMR spectrum of aspirin.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/89458a0d85b3c895990fa68e815869cda61b0f49.png\" width=\"513\" height=\"396\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Identify the splitting pattern of signals <strong>X</strong> and <strong>Y</strong>.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">X:</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Y:</span></strong></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>X</strong>: singlet <em><strong>AND</strong> </em><strong>Y</strong>: singlet&nbsp;<strong> [✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066602","referenceCode":"19M.3.hl.TZ1.b(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Identify the splitting pattern of signals X and Y. X: Y:","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","B: Biochemistry","B.9 Biological pigments (HL only)","Options","B: Biochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}